Package com.reactivecascade.i

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IAction<PHANTOM_OUT>
    A lambda-friendly continuation mOnFireAction which may be run in the future or on a different thread similar to Runnable.
    IActionOne<IN>
    A lambda-friendly functional interface for continuation actions that receive one parameter.
    IActionOneR<IN,OUT>
    A lambda-friendly mOnFireAction which receives two values split returns a getValue
    IActionR<OUT>
    A lambda-friendly functional interface for continuation actions that receive no parameters split return one result.
    IActionTwo<IN1,IN2>
    A lambda-friendly functional interface for subscribe actions which receive two parameters
    IActionTwoR<IN1,IN2,OUT>
    A lambda-friendly functional interface for subscribe actions which receive two parameters
    IAltFuture<IN,OUT>
    One of many possible futures in the multiverse.
    IAspect
    Aspect is combination of thread/typed-group-of-threads AND the program state during which a given piece of asychronous function result or side-effect is desired.
    IAsyncOrigin
    An extendable convenience for debugging asynchronous multithreaded code.
    IBaseAction<PHANTOM_OUT>
    This is a marker interface which other functional interfaces extend
    IBindingContext<T>
    A lifecycle for a reactive or functional relationship
    ICancellable
    Stop an ongoing activity early if it has not already completed.
    ICancellable.State
    An internal-use interface made public to facilitate mixing in alternate implementations.
    ICancellable.StateCancelled
    This is a marker interface.
    ICancellable.StateError
    This is a marker interface.
    IGettable<T>
    Create the actual URL at the last minute, just before the request is processed.
    INamed  
    IReactiveSource<OUT>

    IThreadType
